# Write a function which will load the images from file directory
def load_images_from_folder(folder):
    images = []
    for filename in os.listdir(folder):
        img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(folder,filename))
        if img is not None:
            images.append(img)
    return images

In [55]:
classifier = Sequential()

# 1ST Convolution layer with 32 kernels of 3X3 shape with activation function ReLU
classifier.add(Conv2D(32, (3, 3), input_shape = (224, 224, 3), activation = 'relu'))
classifier.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size = (2, 2)))
classifier.add(Dropout(0.15))

# 2ND another Convolution layer with 64 kernels of 3X3 shape with activation function ReLU
classifier.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation = 'relu'))
classifier.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size = (2, 2)))
classifier.add(Dropout(0.10))

# 3RD another Convolution layer with 64 kernels of 3X3 shape with activation function ReLU
classifier.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation = 'relu'))
classifier.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size = (2, 2)))
classifier.add(Dropout(0.15))

# Flattening the layer before fully connected layers
classifier.add(Flatten())

classifier.add(Dense(units = 512, activation = 'relu'))
classifier.add(Dropout(0.15))

# The final output layer with 12 neuron to predict the categorical classifcation
classifier.add(Dense(units = 15, activation = 'softmax'))
